reviewText: I've seen many of the James Lipton interviews in the old "Inside the Actor's Studio" television broadcasts. Those interviews represent the standard by which I judge all actor interviews. In that context, I only gave the William Shatner interview three stars. While Shatner is interesting, his interviewer, Budd Mishkin failed to elicit the type of responses that James Lipton did with his interviewees.
I really enjoyed this interview.  The tales of his long career and the things he has seen and done are facinating.
I love William Shatner and I thought the interview was wonderful and he has a great sharp wit!
A very interesting interview. It featured rare information regarding Star Trex and Shatner's varied career.
Uninteresting, which is a pity, since I like William Shatner (at least in Boston Legal (et al). This one was boring.
